main event: A UFO was observed at Orlando AFB, Florida on April 5, 1966, and again on April 20, 1966.
interesting points: The first sighting lasted one hour with an object that appeared round and yellowish-orange, drifting 3-5 degrees left-right and moving up and down; the conclusion was it was likely Jupiter, The second sighting was confirmed by two military witnesses who observed a round light pulsating in different colors for 45 minutes, The sightings occurred on clear nights with no unusual weather phenomena reported, Local military and FAA flight agencies reported no unusual visual sightings or radar returns, Both sightings involved detailed observations and descriptions made by credible witnesses.
sighted object: one round light which pulsated in colors, and a yellowish-orange object
witness description: Military personnel, one aeronautical engineer, sincere and credible
